1) Daily routine
-aesthetic vibe to match personality
-photos for inspiration pulled from pinterest
-ability to create list of daily routine
-ability to cross out was was done in that day
-ability to reset the list after 24 hours
-ability to create different sections within the daily routine aka night roughtine/ mourining routine/ spiritual routine


2) Home Cleaning 
-Gives people the ability to create cleaning routines
-you can set up your schedule
-include your products for cleaning
-have notifications for replenishing
-leads you to the amazon site for purchasing

3) Reading Nook
-a book for children with books
-allows parents to lock the screen so that the child can only readd from the app/ an open book
-allows user to create their own story
-allows user to record their voice for a current book
-allows user to hear how a word is proounced

# Daily Routine 
**Mobile:** How uniquely mobile is the product experience?
What makes your app more than a glorified website?
Try for 2 or more of these: maps, camera, location, audio, sensors, push, real-time, etc
-the app will allow users to receive notifications of when it is time to perform that task for self improvement


**Story:** How compelling is the story around this app once completed?
How clear is the value of this app to your audience?
How well would your friends or peers respond to this product idea?
-the app allows users to improve themselves while also gaining inspiration from the accounts that they love to follow

**Market:** How large or unique is the market for this app?
What's the size and scale of your potential user base?
Does this app provide huge value to a niche group of people?
Do you have a well-defined audience of people for this app?
Anyone who is into self improvement, vision boards, aesthetic motivation, and pinterest/instragram/tumblr will find this app interesting. It is a step towards action for their dreams and a constant reminder of the actons that they need to take to improve

**Habit:** How habit-forming or addictive is this app?
How frequently would an average user open and use this app?
Does an average user just consume your app or do they create?
The user would have to open this app everysingle day and at least 1 time per day. This app is for self improvement on every part of the users life, therefore they would be encourage to open it multiple times per day

**Scope:** How well-formed is the scope for this app?
How technically challenging will it be to complete this app by the end of the program?
Is a stripped-down version of this app still interesting to build?
How clearly defined is the product you want to build?
-The first version of this app will be simple, the option to integrate motivational pictures to your routine, add a routine, and get notified about your routine. V2 Will allow video integration and the ability to date routines during the week. so that rahter than it being a daily routine, it can also be a weekly routine.


# Reading Nook
**Mobile:** How uniquely mobile is the product experience?
What makes your app more than a glorified website?
Try for 2 or more of these: maps, camera, location, audio, sensors, push, real-time, etc
-allows parents and users to lock their screen for a period of time. Requiring that the phone or device is not used for anything else other than reading during that time.

**Story:** How compelling is the story around this app once completed?
How clear is the value of this app to your audience?
How well would your friends or peers respond to this product idea?
-the app allows parents to encourage reading in a world where social media and gaming apps dominate the attention of users

**Market:** How large or unique is the market for this app?
What's the size and scale of your potential user base?
Does this app provide huge value to a niche group of people?
Do you have a well-defined audience of people for this app?
-the market of this app is for children under the age of 13. however, over time this app can be increasd to supply reading to older users.

**Habit:** How habit-forming or addictive is this app?
How frequently would an average user open and use this app?
Does an average user just consume your app or do they create?
-this app can be habit forming. The goal is to encourage reading. It can be done so that the device is locked at a specific time as indicated by the parent. Meaning that the only available app for use is the reading nook for a specific period of time.

Scope: How well-formed is the scope for this app?
How technically challenging will it be to complete this app by the end of the program?
Is a stripped-down version of this app still interesting to build?
How clearly defined is the product you want to build?
-Version of this app will include books for children. Parents and kids are able to scroll through and read. V2 will includethe ability for the app to read the text its self. Pressing a word, will cause the app to read it out to the child. V3 will include a locking feature as well as the increase in books for a variety of ages. 

